1
00:00:21,605 --> 00:00:22,940
<i>What are you doing here?</i>

2
00:00:23,023 --> 00:00:25,359
You know you did something wrong,
so you're trying to destroy me.

3
00:00:25,443 --> 00:00:27,361
He was imprisoned in Morocco.

4
00:00:27,445 --> 00:00:29,155
Mateo Crisanto is a criminal.

5
00:00:29,238 --> 00:00:32,199
If they keep digging up the truth
and find out that Gem is Yana,

6
00:00:32,283 --> 00:00:33,659
her life will be in danger.

7
00:00:33,743 --> 00:00:36,328
<i>Maybe they already know</i>
<i>that Gem is Yana.</i>

8
00:00:36,412 --> 00:00:38,539
- What?
- She is Yana Kassir.

9
00:00:38,622 --> 00:00:39,999
<i>There is no doubt that the child is yours.</i>

10
00:00:40,082 --> 00:00:41,959
<i>The baby really is mine.</i>

11
00:00:42,042 --> 00:00:43,419
- Are you okay?
- Yeah. Let's go.

12
00:00:43,919 --> 00:00:45,045
Please don't hurt my brother!

13
00:00:45,129 --> 00:00:47,465
If we don't fight back,
Ace will kill us.

14
00:00:47,548 --> 00:00:48,883
Teo, get in! Hurry!

15
00:00:50,259 --> 00:00:52,136
- I've got Teo.
- Copy, Boss.

16
00:00:52,219 --> 00:00:53,763
<i>Aren't you dead already?</i>

17
00:00:53,846 --> 00:00:55,306
- Gem, where are you?
- Have you left already?

18
00:00:55,389 --> 00:00:57,308
- You knew about this?
- I'll explain everything.

19
00:00:57,391 --> 00:00:58,684
Teo, don't blame Yana.

20
00:00:58,768 --> 00:01:00,394
Why do you two keep lying to me?

21
00:01:02,688 --> 00:01:06,066
♪ <i>Love is never gone... ♪</i>

22
00:01:33,928 --> 00:01:35,554
I'll give you a ride home.

23
00:01:36,013 --> 00:01:38,307
Ace is still looking for you, son.

24
00:01:38,390 --> 00:01:39,767
Stop calling me son!

25
00:01:39,850 --> 00:01:41,393
Did you and Gem plan all of this?

26
00:01:41,477 --> 00:01:44,688
For what? Why?

27
00:01:44,772 --> 00:01:49,276
I didn't know
you were going to Morocco to look for me.

28
00:01:50,820 --> 00:01:54,824
A lot of bad things happened to me, Teo.

29
00:01:55,241 --> 00:01:59,829
I had to protect you and your father
from the Veronas.

30
00:01:59,912 --> 00:02:01,997
You know the Veronas, too?

31
00:02:02,081 --> 00:02:04,333
And what do you mean, "protect"?

32
00:02:04,416 --> 00:02:06,710
It's because you want to forget us!

33
00:02:07,461 --> 00:02:08,796
I came back...

34
00:02:09,463 --> 00:02:11,799
because your lives are in danger.

35
00:02:13,592 --> 00:02:18,180
You have no idea
how worried I am about you.

36
00:02:18,264 --> 00:02:20,099
Drop the act, will you?

37
00:02:21,183 --> 00:02:22,935
What I need from you is the truth.

38
00:02:34,905 --> 00:02:39,451
I applied to work abroad in Dubai.

39
00:02:39,994 --> 00:02:41,829
Your father was against it,

40
00:02:41,912 --> 00:02:44,957
but I was determined
to give us a better life.

41
00:02:46,750 --> 00:02:48,836
But when I arrived in Dubai...

42
00:02:50,129 --> 00:02:54,633
my employer kept exploiting
and harassing me.

43
00:02:55,175 --> 00:02:56,594
Then, when I was able to escape,

44
00:02:56,677 --> 00:02:59,763
someone offered me a job in Italy.

45
00:03:00,222 --> 00:03:01,724
I went with them.

46
00:03:01,807 --> 00:03:07,062
They said they would help me
bring all of you faster.

47
00:03:07,146 --> 00:03:09,481
They promised a higher salary

48
00:03:09,565 --> 00:03:12,192
so we could be together sooner.

49
00:03:13,569 --> 00:03:18,574
I had no idea they were a syndicate.

50
00:03:19,992 --> 00:03:21,410
Instead of taking me to Italy,

51
00:03:21,493 --> 00:03:23,787
they took me to Morocco.

52
00:03:23,871 --> 00:03:26,832
<i>I was forced to work</i>
<i>for a love scam syndicate.</i>

53
00:03:26,916 --> 00:03:28,292
Please let me go!

54
00:03:28,375 --> 00:03:30,044
I will just go back to Dubai!

55
00:03:30,127 --> 00:03:32,379
This is hell! You fooled me!

56
00:03:32,463 --> 00:03:34,840
- Silence! You belong here now!

57
00:03:36,842 --> 00:03:40,429
- Stop!
<i>We had to call men</i>

58
00:03:40,512 --> 00:03:42,389
<i>of different nationalities.</i>

59
00:03:43,307 --> 00:03:48,479
We would befriend them
until we gained their trust,

60
00:03:49,063 --> 00:03:51,398
and then we took all their money.

61
00:03:51,941 --> 00:03:53,275
Sit, sit.

62
00:03:57,696 --> 00:03:59,365
Please let me go.

63
00:03:59,448 --> 00:04:01,241
Please, I beg you.

64
00:04:01,325 --> 00:04:02,785
I will go back to Dubai.

65
00:04:02,868 --> 00:04:04,870
I have to work for my children.

66
00:04:04,954 --> 00:04:07,122
You have to understand something.

67
00:04:08,207 --> 00:04:10,042
You're mine now.

68
00:04:10,125 --> 00:04:14,296
Now, whether this is
pleasurable or painful

69
00:04:15,089 --> 00:04:17,341
is entirely up to you.

70
00:04:18,634 --> 00:04:20,135
But if you behave...

71
00:04:21,553 --> 00:04:23,389
I will be very good to you.

72
00:04:23,472 --> 00:04:25,432
- Sir! Sir! No!

73
00:04:25,516 --> 00:04:27,559
No, sir! Please stop!

74
00:04:27,643 --> 00:04:28,769
-

75
00:04:28,852 --> 00:04:31,188
You're mine!

76
00:04:34,817 --> 00:04:36,151
Hey.

77
00:04:36,860 --> 00:04:38,362
Here.

78
00:04:38,445 --> 00:04:40,864


79
00:04:43,158 --> 00:04:44,243


80
00:04:46,370 --> 00:04:48,205
I'm Nadia.

81
00:04:48,706 --> 00:04:50,791
Help me get out of here.

82
00:04:52,751 --> 00:04:56,130
Many have tried to escape,
but they were all killed.

83
00:04:56,213 --> 00:04:57,715
Believe me.

84
00:04:58,215 --> 00:05:01,969
No one has gotten out of here alive.

85
00:05:02,052 --> 00:05:03,887


86
00:05:06,724 --> 00:05:09,727


87
00:05:12,354 --> 00:05:15,190


88
00:05:18,110 --> 00:05:20,571


89
00:05:23,240 --> 00:05:24,366
She's escaping! Hey!

90
00:05:24,450 --> 00:05:26,660
-

91
00:05:28,787 --> 00:05:33,125
<i>I kept thinking</i>
<i>about you and Issay when I escaped.</i>

92
00:05:34,460 --> 00:05:37,880
-
I told myself...

93
00:05:38,464 --> 00:05:41,050
that I wanted to go back
to the Philippines.

94
00:05:41,133 --> 00:05:43,218
I wanted to see you.

95
00:05:43,302 --> 00:05:46,221
I want to forget everything
that happened to me.

96
00:05:46,305 --> 00:05:47,723
Let me go!

97
00:05:47,806 --> 00:05:49,767
Please, let me go!

98
00:05:49,850 --> 00:05:52,978
Nadia, please help me.
I'm begging you.

99
00:05:54,104 --> 00:05:56,690


100
00:05:58,233 --> 00:06:00,235
There is nowhere to run to.

101
00:06:00,903 --> 00:06:02,905
- Give me the gun.

102
00:06:04,114 --> 00:06:05,699
No! No!

103
00:06:08,577 --> 00:06:10,746
Here. Take out the garbage.

104
00:06:18,629 --> 00:06:22,132
I got this
from the stuff they took from you.

105
00:06:28,931 --> 00:06:30,808

You have no other choice.

106
00:06:30,891 --> 00:06:36,480
Do everything you can to survive.

107
00:06:37,272 --> 00:06:39,691
That way, when the time comes,

108
00:06:40,609 --> 00:06:43,112
you can still be with your family.

109
00:06:43,195 --> 00:06:45,614
It has been a year, Nadia.

110
00:06:45,697 --> 00:06:47,950
I haven't spoken to them since.

111
00:06:48,700 --> 00:06:50,536
They don't know where I am,

112
00:06:50,619 --> 00:06:52,704
or if I'm still alive.

113
00:06:52,788 --> 00:06:54,540
They're probably looking for me.

114
00:06:54,623 --> 00:06:58,961
There are cases where families
get dragged into all this mess.

115
00:06:59,795 --> 00:07:01,797
- So if I were you--
I need to live.

116
00:07:01,880 --> 00:07:04,007
And when I get the chance,

117
00:07:04,091 --> 00:07:07,094
I'll make those monsters pay
for what they did.

118
00:07:10,013 --> 00:07:14,560
They used us to scam rich people.

119
00:07:19,148 --> 00:07:21,150
- Divino.
Pearl.

120
00:07:22,401 --> 00:07:26,572

<i>We blackmailed businessmen and VIPs</i>

121
00:07:26,655 --> 00:07:31,160
<i>to extort and get money from them.</i>

122
00:07:35,998 --> 00:07:37,166


123
00:07:37,249 --> 00:07:39,668


124
00:08:14,328 --> 00:08:17,581
I know what you are
and what they're making you do.

125
00:08:17,664 --> 00:08:20,209
Are you with the police? A detective?

126
00:08:20,292 --> 00:08:23,337
Your boss is my business rival.

127
00:08:23,879 --> 00:08:26,048
He owes me a lot.

128
00:08:28,258 --> 00:08:31,261
Take him down for me.

129
00:08:31,345 --> 00:08:32,971
I want something in return.

130
00:08:33,055 --> 00:08:34,431
Name it.

131
00:08:36,683 --> 00:08:38,018
My freedom.

132
00:08:40,354 --> 00:08:43,190
We'll see.

133
00:08:59,539 --> 00:09:00,999
Come on, let's go!

134
00:09:06,046 --> 00:09:09,007
Nadia, let's go!

135
00:09:13,679 --> 00:09:15,013
Ah! Wait!

136
00:09:15,681 --> 00:09:17,432
Come on! Let's go!

137
00:09:28,277 --> 00:09:31,947
Go, go, go, go, go!

138
00:09:32,030 --> 00:09:34,116
Move, move, move!

139
00:09:44,293 --> 00:09:46,211
Thank you so much.

140
00:09:46,295 --> 00:09:50,841
I am forever indebted to you.

141
00:09:52,092 --> 00:09:54,845
<i>I called your father several times...</i>

142
00:09:55,887 --> 00:09:58,390
but he wouldn't answer my calls.

143
00:09:58,473 --> 00:10:01,852
I don't even know
if I should believe what you're saying.

144
00:10:03,687 --> 00:10:06,273
Now's your time
to explain everything to me.

145
00:10:06,356 --> 00:10:08,483
And please stop trying
to justify yourself.

146
00:10:09,067 --> 00:10:11,153
Because no matter what you say,

147
00:10:11,236 --> 00:10:14,573
it won't change the fact
that you lied and abandoned us!

148
00:10:15,282 --> 00:10:18,618
From now on,
you will all work for me.

149
00:10:18,702 --> 00:10:21,413
You cannot go home to your country.

150
00:10:21,788 --> 00:10:23,832
- You two. Let's go. Come on.
- Go!

151
00:10:23,915 --> 00:10:25,042
Go!

152
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:35,135
So, you brought me here
to make me one of them?

153
00:10:35,218 --> 00:10:37,637
- You lied to me!
- No.

154
00:10:38,096 --> 00:10:42,184
Didn't I tell you we'll see
if you could earn your freedom?

155
00:10:44,644 --> 00:10:46,646
So you'll have me locked up here, too?

156
00:10:46,730 --> 00:10:48,982
As much as I want you to stay...

157
00:10:49,941 --> 00:10:51,109
you are free now.

158
00:10:53,862 --> 00:10:55,280
You're free to go.

159
00:10:56,406 --> 00:10:57,908
<i> I got my freedom...</i>

160
00:10:58,950 --> 00:11:00,702
but I had nowhere to go.

161
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:06,083
Many have pretended to help me,

162
00:11:06,166 --> 00:11:08,168
but they used me too.

163
00:11:13,507 --> 00:11:15,509
I have nowhere to go.

164
00:11:17,010 --> 00:11:19,679
I have no home to go back to
in the Philippines.

165
00:11:29,648 --> 00:11:31,400
I'll stay here with you.

166
00:11:34,111 --> 00:11:36,279
You worked for Divino

167
00:11:36,363 --> 00:11:37,948
and helped him run a syndicate?

168
00:11:39,074 --> 00:11:41,076
I had nowhere to go.

169
00:11:41,159 --> 00:11:42,244
No, that's not true!

170
00:11:42,327 --> 00:11:44,371
There was a way to get out
if you wanted to.

171
00:11:45,747 --> 00:11:48,583
Just admit you wouldn't leave
because Divino is giving you

172
00:11:48,667 --> 00:11:50,210
a luxurious and comfortable life!

173
00:11:50,293 --> 00:11:53,797
Divino can't know that I have a family,
and that I'm connected to you.

174
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:56,007
It would put you all in danger.

175
00:11:57,300 --> 00:12:01,221
I couldn't bring myself to face you...

176
00:12:04,349 --> 00:12:08,520
because I sold my soul to the devil.

177
00:12:09,938 --> 00:12:13,525
I've become a devil, like them.

178
00:12:15,110 --> 00:12:18,697
You know, all I hear from you is excuses.

179
00:12:19,990 --> 00:12:22,325
I don't feel anything anymore

180
00:12:22,409 --> 00:12:25,412
because everything you've done
is still affecting us.

181
00:12:25,495 --> 00:12:27,622
This is all your fault.

182
00:12:27,706 --> 00:12:30,584
If you hadn't left us,
I wouldn't have gone to work in Morocco.

183
00:12:30,667 --> 00:12:34,004
I wouldn't have gone to jail,
and none of this would have happened.

184
00:12:35,672 --> 00:12:37,424
Let me help you.

185
00:12:39,968 --> 00:12:42,053
This will be our last conversation.

186
00:12:43,805 --> 00:12:45,724
You've changed, and I've changed too.

187
00:12:48,894 --> 00:12:50,562
I'm not afraid anymore.

188
00:13:22,802 --> 00:13:24,638
Oh. Son.

189
00:13:33,146 --> 00:13:35,565
What happened to you?
Why do you look like that?

190
00:13:37,442 --> 00:13:38,693
It's nothing, Pa.

191
00:13:38,777 --> 00:13:41,655
Oh, come on.

192
00:13:42,656 --> 00:13:47,494
It seems you're already
risking your life for Gem.

193
00:13:50,038 --> 00:13:51,289
Where is she, anyway?

194
00:13:53,667 --> 00:13:54,918
Is there a problem?

195
00:13:59,589 --> 00:14:03,718
Son, we both know
you can't hide anything from me.

196
00:14:04,803 --> 00:14:08,056
And we don't want
to keep secrets from each other.

197
00:14:08,139 --> 00:14:09,724
So come on, say it.

198
00:14:10,559 --> 00:14:12,310
I won't stop until you do.

199
00:14:13,395 --> 00:14:14,479
Pa...

200
00:14:24,531 --> 00:14:26,116
Mama is alive.

201
00:14:36,751 --> 00:14:38,503
Not this again, son.

202
00:14:38,920 --> 00:14:40,255
It's true, Pa.

203
00:14:40,338 --> 00:14:43,049
I saw her and talked to her.

204
00:14:44,384 --> 00:14:46,303
Is that true, Teo?

205
00:14:46,386 --> 00:14:47,721
Mama is still alive?

206
00:14:50,765 --> 00:14:52,434
She's different now.

207
00:14:54,144 --> 00:14:55,395
She's rich...

208
00:14:57,147 --> 00:14:58,815
and working for Divino.

209
00:15:04,487 --> 00:15:05,655
What?

210
00:15:07,574 --> 00:15:08,742
Since when?

211
00:15:10,827 --> 00:15:12,996
- Where is she?
- Enough, Pa.

212
00:15:15,123 --> 00:15:17,959
Whatever you want to say,
I already told her.

213
00:15:18,835 --> 00:15:21,504
She won't show herself again.
She won't bother us anymore.

214
00:15:21,963 --> 00:15:23,214
Good!

215
00:15:25,800 --> 00:15:29,304
Good! I don't ever want to even see
her shadow.

216
00:15:30,764 --> 00:15:32,849
She's been dead to me for a long time.

217
00:15:33,642 --> 00:15:34,476
To us.

218
00:16:03,254 --> 00:16:04,339
Liar!

219
00:16:09,094 --> 00:16:12,597
Then and now.

220
00:16:14,182 --> 00:16:16,935
You'll probably be a liar
until the day I die.

221
00:16:25,318 --> 00:16:26,778
I'll explain. Listen...

222
00:16:26,861 --> 00:16:28,655
You listen to me!

223
00:16:30,365 --> 00:16:32,617
I've thought about
everything that has happened.

224
00:16:33,743 --> 00:16:35,662
You're such a good liar.

225
00:16:36,621 --> 00:16:38,623
You know, I shouldn't have doubted

226
00:16:38,707 --> 00:16:40,250
that you and my mother
are working together

227
00:16:40,333 --> 00:16:41,751
because you're the same!

228
00:16:41,835 --> 00:16:44,629
- You both betrayed your family.
- I didn't betray you.

229
00:16:46,297 --> 00:16:48,049
Circumstances drove us apart.

230
00:16:48,133 --> 00:16:50,051
I've always been honest with you, right?

231
00:16:50,135 --> 00:16:53,054
- Because you have no choice.
- Because I don't want to lie anymore!

232
00:16:53,138 --> 00:16:54,889
I don't want to fool you anymore.

233
00:16:55,974 --> 00:16:58,059
Why didn't you tell me
that my mother was alive?

234
00:16:58,143 --> 00:17:00,061
And what good would that have done?

235
00:17:00,854 --> 00:17:04,190
Your mother's involved
in the Veronas' illegal businesses.

236
00:17:04,858 --> 00:17:06,443
If you reconnect with her,

237
00:17:07,068 --> 00:17:08,528
you'll just get yourself in trouble.

238
00:17:11,948 --> 00:17:13,783
You're even saying
the same thing she said.

239
00:17:13,867 --> 00:17:16,661
Did you two plan this?

240
00:17:16,745 --> 00:17:19,330
My mother's the one who knows your mother.

241
00:17:19,414 --> 00:17:21,124
They planned this.

242
00:17:21,207 --> 00:17:24,586
They told me not to tell you
that your mother was alive.

243
00:17:24,669 --> 00:17:27,005
That's why I agreed to take you
to that grave back then.

244
00:17:27,630 --> 00:17:28,840
How about now, Gem?

245
00:17:29,591 --> 00:17:32,177
We've known each other for a long time.
We've been through so much together.

246
00:17:32,260 --> 00:17:33,970
- Why didn't you tell me?
- Because if the Veronas

247
00:17:34,053 --> 00:17:35,513
find out that you're her son,

248
00:17:35,597 --> 00:17:38,266
that you two are related,
and you've infiltrated their lives,

249
00:17:38,349 --> 00:17:39,517
Divino will kill you.

250
00:17:39,601 --> 00:17:41,227
Well, we're going to die anyway.

251
00:17:41,311 --> 00:17:44,981
You know, I was ready to die for you.

252
00:17:45,064 --> 00:17:46,316
But here we go again.

253
00:17:46,399 --> 00:17:48,443
You never change.

254
00:17:48,526 --> 00:17:50,195
You didn't look for her.

255
00:17:50,862 --> 00:17:52,197
You never thought about her.

256
00:17:52,989 --> 00:17:54,866
You had moved on.
You had already found peace.

257
00:17:54,949 --> 00:17:56,576
What right did I have to ruin it?

258
00:17:57,202 --> 00:18:01,039
Your mother told me
not to tell you that she was alive.

259
00:18:01,122 --> 00:18:03,917
I promised her I wouldn't.
I gave her my word.

260
00:18:04,501 --> 00:18:06,586
I don't have bad intentions, Teo.

261
00:18:07,378 --> 00:18:09,214
So, if it weren't for what happened,

262
00:18:09,297 --> 00:18:10,799
I would never have found out
she's still alive?

263
00:18:10,882 --> 00:18:13,343
There was never supposed to be
any trouble in the first place.

264
00:18:13,426 --> 00:18:15,261
Your mother was helping me
escape from the Veronas

265
00:18:15,345 --> 00:18:16,679
because we had a deal.

266
00:18:16,763 --> 00:18:18,807
We don't want
to ruin your life anymore, Teo.

267
00:18:20,892 --> 00:18:22,811
You have no obligation to me.

268
00:18:30,610 --> 00:18:31,694
Ace...

269
00:18:35,949 --> 00:18:37,617
Ace is the father of my baby.

270
00:18:40,078 --> 00:18:42,664
I'll raise my child on my own.

271
00:18:43,498 --> 00:18:45,291
I know I'm not perfect.

272
00:18:45,375 --> 00:18:48,294
But I'll raise my child
to be a good person.

273
00:18:49,671 --> 00:18:52,757
And I'm not going to let it meet
its demon father.

274
00:18:54,384 --> 00:18:55,969
Just leave me be, Teo.

275
00:18:57,679 --> 00:18:59,514
I told you, didn't I?

276
00:19:00,056 --> 00:19:03,309
No matter who the father is,
I'll support you.

277
00:19:04,310 --> 00:19:06,312
It's just hard to believe you...

278
00:19:06,396 --> 00:19:08,439
because you're full of secrets and lies.

279
00:19:08,523 --> 00:19:11,693
I don't even know if I should believe
that Ace is really your child's father.

280
00:19:11,776 --> 00:19:14,571
You could just be telling me that
so I'd let you go.

281
00:19:24,789 --> 00:19:27,458
Ace really is the father of my child.

282
00:19:43,474 --> 00:19:44,893
Do you love me, Gem?

283
00:19:51,733 --> 00:19:53,151
I love you so much.

284
00:19:53,902 --> 00:19:55,486
Really?

285
00:19:57,196 --> 00:19:58,364
You mean it this time?

286
00:19:59,824 --> 00:20:01,242
You won't hurt me anymore?

287
00:20:02,327 --> 00:20:03,912
You won't deceive me anymore?

288
00:20:06,789 --> 00:20:08,291
Because I'm tired.

289
00:20:10,543 --> 00:20:12,211
I'm tired of doubting you.

290
00:20:14,547 --> 00:20:16,466
I'm tired of trying to find the truth

291
00:20:16,549 --> 00:20:18,551
in every word
that comes out of your mouth.

292
00:20:21,095 --> 00:20:23,598
Here I am, still...

293
00:20:26,059 --> 00:20:27,560
I can't bear to lose you.

294
00:20:29,687 --> 00:20:32,273
Even if you hurt me over and over again...

295
00:20:34,525 --> 00:20:37,695
Even if you lie until my last breath...

296
00:20:37,779 --> 00:20:39,864
I'll still stand by you.

297
00:20:39,948 --> 00:20:42,116
I'll support your child.

298
00:20:42,700 --> 00:20:44,535
Because that's how much I love you.

299
00:20:46,663 --> 00:20:48,247
Even if it ruins me.

300
00:20:52,335 --> 00:20:53,378
Teo...

301
00:21:16,609 --> 00:21:19,612
<i>Authorities are still verifying the motive</i>

302
00:21:19,696 --> 00:21:21,572
<i>behind the commotion</i>
<i>caused by Judge Divino Verona's son,</i>

303
00:21:21,656 --> 00:21:24,867
<i>who was also recently linked</i>
<i>to a human trafficking case.</i>

304
00:21:24,951 --> 00:21:29,580
Why don't we just bribe that reporter
so he'd leave us alone?

305
00:21:29,664 --> 00:21:31,499
People saw you, Ace.

306
00:21:32,083 --> 00:21:34,002
Of course, that will be in the news.

307
00:21:34,460 --> 00:21:35,878
You even pulled out a gun.

308
00:21:35,962 --> 00:21:37,714
What were you even thinking?

309
00:21:38,089 --> 00:21:41,592
My wife and unborn child were taken, Pa.
That's what I was thinking!

310
00:21:41,676 --> 00:21:45,179
Divino,
why are you blaming your own son?

311
00:21:45,680 --> 00:21:49,100
Who wouldn't lose control

312
00:21:49,183 --> 00:21:52,353
after seeing his wife and child
being taken by her lover?

313
00:21:52,812 --> 00:21:54,647
You can't blame your son.

314
00:21:55,314 --> 00:21:56,733
Where are you going?

315
00:21:56,816 --> 00:21:58,234
I'm going to find my wife and child.

316
00:21:58,317 --> 00:21:59,694
I'm bringing Gem back here.

317
00:21:59,777 --> 00:22:01,279
Home where she belongs.

318
00:22:01,362 --> 00:22:02,822
She doesn't belong here.

319
00:22:02,905 --> 00:22:04,574
She's not yours, Ace.

320
00:22:06,826 --> 00:22:08,578
What do you mean?

321
00:22:08,661 --> 00:22:11,956
Gem and Teo knew each other in Morocco.

322
00:22:13,041 --> 00:22:14,917
Gem is Yana Kassir,

323
00:22:15,001 --> 00:22:18,129
the woman involved
in a robbery incident with Teo.

324
00:22:18,212 --> 00:22:20,339
Gem was Teo's girlfriend...

325
00:22:20,423 --> 00:22:23,426
...who became
Gem Ybañez when she was released.

326
00:22:23,509 --> 00:22:25,011
She used you.

327
00:22:25,678 --> 00:22:27,180
She fooled you.

328
00:22:28,222 --> 00:22:29,891
Well, all of us.

329
00:22:34,771 --> 00:22:40,026
Now, try to remember
how Gem was able to include Teo

330
00:22:40,109 --> 00:22:41,944
on the list of those
who were released in Morocco.

331
00:22:42,695 --> 00:22:45,114
Who else could have helped you?

332
00:22:47,241 --> 00:22:48,576
I don't know. I can't remember.

333
00:22:48,659 --> 00:22:51,996
It can be a friend,
an acquaintance, or a family member.

334
00:22:52,080 --> 00:22:55,083
Surely someone among them
knows where they are.

335
00:23:13,017 --> 00:23:15,019
I've been trying to reach you.

336
00:23:15,728 --> 00:23:16,979
Where have you been?

337
00:23:18,606 --> 00:23:19,774
Work.

338
00:23:21,984 --> 00:23:24,237
I had to sort things out
for the Myanmar shipment.

339
00:23:24,320 --> 00:23:25,988
Is there a problem?

340
00:23:29,867 --> 00:23:31,869
I just want to unwind.

341
00:23:33,204 --> 00:23:34,455
Family problem?

342
00:23:36,249 --> 00:23:37,667
I'm listening.

343
00:23:39,252 --> 00:23:40,878
Is it about Ace?

344
00:23:41,879 --> 00:23:43,965
I don't want to talk about it.

345
00:23:46,384 --> 00:23:48,219
If you want...

346
00:23:50,680 --> 00:23:53,933
I can take charge of the businesses
for now.

347
00:23:55,726 --> 00:23:59,230
Take care of your family problem first.

348
00:24:00,565 --> 00:24:01,899
I heard...

349
00:24:03,109 --> 00:24:05,027
it's getting worse.

350
00:24:12,118 --> 00:24:14,203
I can always count on you.

351
00:24:34,182 --> 00:24:35,183
Hello?

352
00:24:35,266 --> 00:24:38,811
It's too dangerous for Teo to help you.

353
00:24:39,395 --> 00:24:40,980
<i>Stick to our plan.</i>

354
00:24:41,439 --> 00:24:43,858
I'll help you sneak out of the country.

355
00:24:45,276 --> 00:24:48,696
Teo and I agreed
that we won't leave each other.

356
00:24:49,614 --> 00:24:51,365
I have to keep my word.

357
00:24:51,449 --> 00:24:52,909
He'd get hurt.

358
00:24:52,992 --> 00:24:54,785
He'll be in danger

359
00:24:54,869 --> 00:24:57,038
if you try to escape with them.

360
00:24:57,580 --> 00:25:00,750
No matter what happens,
we'll stay together.

361
00:25:00,833 --> 00:25:02,877
I will still help you.

362
00:25:02,960 --> 00:25:04,629
I got you involved with the Veronas.

363
00:25:04,712 --> 00:25:06,339
Let me get you out.

364
00:25:07,381 --> 00:25:09,634
I will still protect you.

365
00:25:10,843 --> 00:25:11,928
Thank you.

366
00:25:27,985 --> 00:25:29,862
Pa, Teo...

367
00:25:30,863 --> 00:25:32,949
I want to see Mama.

368
00:25:33,032 --> 00:25:34,116
Issay.

369
00:25:35,868 --> 00:25:38,037
Don't ever say that again.

370
00:25:38,120 --> 00:25:41,832
Pa, despite what happened,
she's still your wife.

371
00:25:41,916 --> 00:25:43,417
She is still our mother.

372
00:25:43,501 --> 00:25:47,880
She wasn't a good mother or wife.

373
00:25:47,964 --> 00:25:50,508
She's not here. She's not in our lives.

374
00:25:50,591 --> 00:25:53,135
So enough. It's over.
We're done with her.

375
00:25:53,219 --> 00:25:56,514
If you don't want to see her,
I'll see her myself,

376
00:25:56,597 --> 00:25:58,432
even if just for a moment.

377
00:25:58,975 --> 00:26:00,643
She'll only brainwash you.

378
00:26:01,519 --> 00:26:03,729
She'll make up lies

379
00:26:03,813 --> 00:26:06,983
in order to get you
and take you away from us.

380
00:26:08,401 --> 00:26:10,152
You don't know her, Issay.

381
00:26:10,236 --> 00:26:11,737
We don't know her.

382
00:26:11,821 --> 00:26:13,948
Stop looking for her.

383
00:26:14,031 --> 00:26:15,783
It's not like you grew up with her.

384
00:26:15,866 --> 00:26:17,785
Exactly, Teo!

385
00:26:17,868 --> 00:26:19,912
You got to be with her,

386
00:26:20,496 --> 00:26:22,415
but I didn't!

387
00:26:22,498 --> 00:26:24,000
I didn't!

388
00:26:24,083 --> 00:26:27,545
I'm jealous of my friends
who have mothers...

389
00:26:27,628 --> 00:26:30,548
...who love them so much.

390
00:26:31,048 --> 00:26:33,384
Your mother doesn't love you!

391
00:26:33,467 --> 00:26:36,095
She left you when you were just a baby!

392
00:26:40,474 --> 00:26:43,227
Issay! Come back here!

393
00:26:49,900 --> 00:26:51,902
Your mother is such a pain in the neck.

394
00:26:51,986 --> 00:26:54,405
She's causing trouble even now.

395
00:26:55,072 --> 00:26:56,407
Honestly, Pa...

396
00:26:58,826 --> 00:27:00,995
Mama said a lot of things,

397
00:27:02,955 --> 00:27:04,957
but she never mentioned you and Issay.

398
00:27:05,791 --> 00:27:09,545
I guess she really wants
nothing to do with our family.

399
00:27:10,504 --> 00:27:12,715
Teo, Mr. Alonzo,
have you guys seen this?

400
00:27:12,798 --> 00:27:13,716
Seen what?

401
00:27:13,799 --> 00:27:17,720
<i> Attorney Ace Verona</i>
<i>used his grit and the claws of the law</i>

402
00:27:17,803 --> 00:27:21,515
<i>against the suspects involved</i>
<i>in his wife's abduction.</i>

403
00:27:21,599 --> 00:27:25,269
<i>Mateo Crisanto was formally charged</i>
<i>with kidnapping</i>

404
00:27:25,353 --> 00:27:29,190
<i>the wife of Attorney Ace Verona.</i>

405
00:27:29,273 --> 00:27:33,944
<i>Guillermo "Gimo" Magno</i>
<i>is also facing charges</i>

406
00:27:34,028 --> 00:27:37,406
<i>with being an accessory to the crime.</i>

407
00:27:37,490 --> 00:27:41,619
<i>It can be remembered</i>
<i>that the Verona couple</i>

408
00:27:41,702 --> 00:27:45,664
<i>was in the news</i>
<i>after they gave 40 million pesos</i>

409
00:27:45,748 --> 00:27:48,167
<i>in ransom when they were abducted.</i>

410
00:27:48,250 --> 00:27:51,087
<i>With this, they issued</i>
<i>a 10-million-peso reward</i>

411
00:27:51,170 --> 00:27:53,798
<i>to anyone who knows the whereabouts</i>

412
00:27:53,881 --> 00:27:57,134
<i>of Mateo Crisanto and his accomplice,</i>

413
00:27:57,218 --> 00:27:58,886
<i>Guillermo "Gimo" Magno.</i>

414
00:28:03,391 --> 00:28:05,309
Teo, you have a phone call.

415
00:28:29,375 --> 00:28:30,459
Teo!

416
00:28:37,967 --> 00:28:39,135
<i>Teo.</i>

417
00:28:41,720 --> 00:28:43,889
<i>Please answer. This is important.</i>

418
00:28:43,973 --> 00:28:46,976
<i>Divino is looking</i>
<i>for everyone connected to you.</i>

419
00:28:47,977 --> 00:28:49,645
Please, son.

420
00:28:50,646 --> 00:28:52,398
Please talk to me.

421
00:28:53,732 --> 00:28:54,775
M-Ma?

422
00:28:57,987 --> 00:29:00,573
Ma, it's Issay.

423
00:29:01,657 --> 00:29:03,409
Why do you have Teo's phone?

424
00:29:04,285 --> 00:29:05,619
Where's your brother?

425
00:29:05,703 --> 00:29:11,208
Ma, can I see you, just for a moment?

426
00:29:11,292 --> 00:29:12,960
Please, Ma.

427
00:29:15,045 --> 00:29:17,214
<i>Don't you want to see me?</i>

428
00:29:17,715 --> 00:29:20,551
I was still a baby when you left.

429
00:29:20,634 --> 00:29:23,888
You know, Ma, I'm grown-up now.

430
00:29:26,974 --> 00:29:27,975
I'll go now, Ma.

431
00:29:28,058 --> 00:29:30,644
Let's just call each other, okay?

432
00:29:32,146 --> 00:29:35,065
Don't use your brother's phone.

433
00:29:35,691 --> 00:29:37,109
Give me your number.

434
00:29:37,193 --> 00:29:43,657
0917841121.

435
00:29:44,366 --> 00:29:45,451
Ma.

436
00:29:46,285 --> 00:29:51,123
Even though I haven't seen you
or met you yet...

437
00:29:51,207 --> 00:29:54,168
...I love you so much.

438
00:30:02,009 --> 00:30:03,052
Issay?

439
00:30:08,224 --> 00:30:09,642
Teo.

440
00:30:42,466 --> 00:30:43,467
Teo.

441
00:30:43,551 --> 00:30:46,262
Why did you call? What for?

442
00:30:46,345 --> 00:30:47,972
<i>What did you tell Issay?</i>

443
00:30:48,055 --> 00:30:49,473
Did you brainwash her?

444
00:30:49,557 --> 00:30:51,058
No.

445
00:30:51,141 --> 00:30:53,227
It's you I wanted to talk to.

446
00:30:53,769 --> 00:30:55,521
Please leave Issay alone.

447
00:30:56,689 --> 00:30:58,023
She'll end up getting hurt.

448
00:30:58,107 --> 00:31:00,025
I'd never do that.

449
00:31:00,568 --> 00:31:02,152
<i>Teo, listen to me.</i>

450
00:31:02,236 --> 00:31:04,738
Divino is getting close to finding you.

451
00:31:05,406 --> 00:31:07,992
Don't let your father and Issay
out of the house.

452
00:31:08,075 --> 00:31:09,660
Leave Gem to me.

453
00:31:09,743 --> 00:31:12,496
I can protect them, especially Gem.

454
00:31:13,038 --> 00:31:14,707
<i>Don't get involved.</i>

455
00:31:14,790 --> 00:31:16,500
Just worry about yourself.

456
00:31:16,584 --> 00:31:20,004
You'll get into serious trouble
if Divino finds out I'm your son.

457
00:31:33,475 --> 00:31:35,144
I have it sorted out.

458
00:31:36,020 --> 00:31:37,938
I've got passports for your family.

459
00:31:38,647 --> 00:31:42,234
They're Malaysian passports,
not Philippine passports.

460
00:31:42,318 --> 00:31:45,613
It'll be easier to sneak out
of the country if we're foreigners.

461
00:31:47,656 --> 00:31:50,117
We're going to Vietnam and wait there
until things cool down a bit.

462
00:31:50,200 --> 00:31:51,619
Have you told them already?

463
00:31:52,536 --> 00:31:53,704
Not yet.

464
00:31:53,787 --> 00:31:55,539
Why haven't you told them?

465
00:31:55,623 --> 00:31:57,166
We're running out of time.

466
00:31:57,249 --> 00:31:59,084
I was thinking
I could still fix everything.

467
00:31:59,168 --> 00:32:02,671
Maybe I can still do something
so they won't have to go into hiding.

468
00:32:02,755 --> 00:32:03,881
Teo, listen to me.

469
00:32:04,423 --> 00:32:05,841
Judge Divino is different.

470
00:32:06,800 --> 00:32:08,886
He's not like Ace, who's all talk.

471
00:32:09,511 --> 00:32:11,138
I'll go cook that corn.

472
00:32:11,221 --> 00:32:12,556
Don't overcook it, okay?

473
00:32:12,640 --> 00:32:14,224
- Should I just boil it?
- Yes.

474
00:32:15,726 --> 00:32:18,771
Sooner or later,
they'll find out your connection to Boss.

475
00:32:18,854 --> 00:32:20,356
To Pearl.

476
00:32:20,439 --> 00:32:23,108
And when that happens,
it's not just Ace who will throw a fit.

477
00:32:23,192 --> 00:32:25,110
Judge Divino will be furious too.

478
00:32:26,278 --> 00:32:28,697
And that's what you should be afraid of.

479
00:32:29,657 --> 00:32:31,992
He's not like Ace, who's all talk.

480
00:32:33,202 --> 00:32:36,789
Judge Divino is quiet but deadly.

481
00:32:39,792 --> 00:32:42,211
And even if he goes to jail,

482
00:32:42,294 --> 00:32:44,380
he can still have your family killed.

483
00:32:45,089 --> 00:32:46,507
He has lots of connections.

484
00:32:46,965 --> 00:32:49,885
He can have you or your family killed,
no matter where you are.

485
00:32:53,472 --> 00:32:55,891
So let's leave while we still have money

486
00:32:55,974 --> 00:32:57,643
and while we're still alive.

487
00:32:58,185 --> 00:32:59,520
How much money do we need?

488
00:32:59,603 --> 00:33:01,438
There's only five million pesos left.

489
00:33:01,522 --> 00:33:03,941
I have some money saved.
It's enough for all of us.

490
00:33:04,024 --> 00:33:06,026
That's your money. We can't use it.

491
00:33:06,110 --> 00:33:08,737
Teo, I saved that money for my escape.

492
00:33:09,321 --> 00:33:10,739
So let's use it.

493
00:33:16,954 --> 00:33:18,622
You have to tell them, okay?

494
00:33:27,005 --> 00:33:28,799
What are you doing there, Larajean?

495
00:33:28,882 --> 00:33:31,552
You still have lots of books here.

496
00:33:31,635 --> 00:33:33,262
It'd be a shame to just leave them here.

497
00:33:33,345 --> 00:33:36,223
Teo told me to bring only what I need.

498
00:33:36,765 --> 00:33:41,103
Do-- Do you need anything else
from your stuff here?

499
00:33:41,186 --> 00:33:42,813
Where are you? I'll bring them to you.

500
00:33:43,647 --> 00:33:44,815
No need, Larajean.

501
00:33:45,774 --> 00:33:47,276
I won't tell anyone else.

502
00:33:47,359 --> 00:33:49,111
I'll keep it a secret.

503
00:33:50,571 --> 00:33:52,906
<i>It's really fine. Don't bother yourself.</i>

504
00:33:55,701 --> 00:33:57,286
Okay, if you say so.

505
00:33:58,871 --> 00:34:01,623
Just call me if you need anything.

506
00:34:01,707 --> 00:34:04,418
If you need someone to talk to
or if you have a problem,

507
00:34:04,501 --> 00:34:06,420
just call me, okay?

508
00:34:38,911 --> 00:34:39,995
Hey!

509
00:34:43,123 --> 00:34:45,626
- Who are you?
- Well, who are you?

510
00:34:45,709 --> 00:34:47,419
Do you know Yana and Teo?

511
00:34:47,503 --> 00:34:48,754
Yana?

512
00:34:49,505 --> 00:34:50,422
You mean Gem?

513
00:34:50,506 --> 00:34:53,550
Tell me where they are,
and you won't get hurt.

514
00:34:53,634 --> 00:34:54,968
I don't know.

515
00:34:55,636 --> 00:34:57,304
I'm looking for them too.

516
00:34:57,387 --> 00:34:59,681
What do you want from Teo and Gem?

517
00:34:59,765 --> 00:35:01,600
How did you know Gem is Yana?

518
00:35:02,267 --> 00:35:05,521
They got me in trouble
when we were in Morocco.

519
00:35:06,063 --> 00:35:07,564
Damn that Chameleon!

520
00:35:09,817 --> 00:35:12,694
- I can help you.
- Really?

521
00:35:12,778 --> 00:35:15,447
We can work together.

522
00:35:24,873 --> 00:35:27,709
Mr. Handsome, here's your order.

523
00:35:28,961 --> 00:35:30,587
Mister, can you give me money to buy food?

524
00:35:30,671 --> 00:35:32,714
- Go away!
- Please, I'm hungry.

525
00:35:32,798 --> 00:35:34,800
- Go away!
- Please, mister.

526
00:35:34,883 --> 00:35:37,052
- All good. Yeah.
- Come back, okay?

527
00:35:37,135 --> 00:35:39,012
Stop bugging me! Go away!

528
00:35:39,096 --> 00:35:40,514
I said go away!

529
00:35:40,597 --> 00:35:42,182
Mister, please spare me some change.

530
00:35:42,266 --> 00:35:44,685
- Go away! I have no money!
- Mister, please.

531
00:35:44,768 --> 00:35:45,769
He's gone.

532
00:35:46,728 --> 00:35:47,938
Where is he?

533
00:35:58,156 --> 00:35:59,241
Miss.

534
00:36:00,033 --> 00:36:02,703
Have you seen the guy
who was wearing a jacket before?

535
00:36:02,786 --> 00:36:05,038
- Oh, the handsome guy?
- Yes.

536
00:36:05,122 --> 00:36:08,375
He's new here,
and he parks his motorcycle here.

537
00:36:08,458 --> 00:36:09,459
Why?

538
00:36:10,085 --> 00:36:12,004
Did you see where he went?

539
00:36:12,546 --> 00:36:14,631
He scratched my car.

540
00:36:14,715 --> 00:36:17,634
He ran away,
and I saw his motorcycle heading here.

541
00:36:17,718 --> 00:36:19,469
Sorry, I don't know.

542
00:36:24,099 --> 00:36:25,934
Here. This might help you remember.

543
00:36:26,435 --> 00:36:27,853
Oh, he's at Gumamela Street.

544
00:36:32,649 --> 00:36:33,483
<i>Larajean?</i>

545
00:36:33,567 --> 00:36:35,527
Hello, Mr. Alonzo?

546
00:36:35,611 --> 00:36:36,778
Wh-where's Teo?

547
00:36:36,862 --> 00:36:38,405
What do you need from him?

548
00:36:38,488 --> 00:36:42,951
I went to your house to get Issay's books,

549
00:36:43,452 --> 00:36:47,456
and then I bumped into a man
at the workshop.

550
00:36:47,539 --> 00:36:51,126
He pointed a gun at me and hit me.

551
00:36:51,209 --> 00:36:52,794
He was looking for Teo

552
00:36:52,878 --> 00:36:55,172
<i>and left an address.</i>

553
00:36:55,255 --> 00:36:57,883
He said he needs to talk to Teo

554
00:36:57,966 --> 00:37:01,178
and bring him something he needs.

555
00:37:45,180 --> 00:37:46,598
Go on, try it.

556
00:37:48,016 --> 00:37:49,851
Long time no see, Chameleon.

557
00:37:50,978 --> 00:37:51,979
Where's the money?

558
00:37:52,062 --> 00:37:53,063
Teo.

559
00:38:06,326 --> 00:38:07,744
This is so small!

560
00:38:07,828 --> 00:38:09,204
That's a million!

561
00:38:09,913 --> 00:38:10,747
Is this all?

562
00:38:10,831 --> 00:38:13,291
I flew from Morocco for this?

563
00:38:13,375 --> 00:38:15,502
We ran out of money.

564
00:38:15,585 --> 00:38:19,172
We've spent all of it.
What did you expect us to do?

565
00:38:19,256 --> 00:38:21,341
If you don't want it, then give it back!

566
00:38:21,425 --> 00:38:23,552
No. This is mine.

567
00:38:29,975 --> 00:38:30,976
Hello.

568
00:38:32,561 --> 00:38:34,646
Send me the ten million.

569
00:38:35,188 --> 00:38:36,440
The criminals you're looking for are here.

570
00:38:37,024 --> 00:38:38,358
This bastard.

571
00:39:13,643 --> 00:39:16,229
What problem did you cause this time?

572
00:39:17,105 --> 00:39:21,193
I had my men follow Gem and Teo
to the place you said they were in!

573
00:39:21,276 --> 00:39:24,780
But all they found
was your beaten-up minion.

574
00:39:25,280 --> 00:39:26,865
Judge, I'm sorry.

575
00:39:26,948 --> 00:39:29,034
The timing was just a bit off,

576
00:39:29,117 --> 00:39:30,494
or you would've caught them.

577
00:39:30,577 --> 00:39:32,454
God! You're unbelievable!

578
00:39:32,537 --> 00:39:34,414
B-but I have more information

579
00:39:34,498 --> 00:39:37,501
about the location of Ronnie's motorcycle.
He's Teo's friend.

580
00:39:37,584 --> 00:39:41,129
I'm sure they're hiding around that area.

581
00:39:41,213 --> 00:39:42,214
Where is that?

582
00:40:12,494 --> 00:40:13,745
No one is here, sir.

583
00:40:19,918 --> 00:40:22,087
I can't believe you have the audacity

584
00:40:22,170 --> 00:40:24,339
to parade your incompetence to my face!

585
00:40:25,465 --> 00:40:27,134
Get out of my face!

586
00:40:27,217 --> 00:40:28,718
B-but sir...

587
00:40:28,802 --> 00:40:30,428
W-why are you mad at me?

588
00:40:30,512 --> 00:40:35,183
I worked hard on my own
just to look for them.

589
00:40:35,267 --> 00:40:38,019
I had someone follow them.
It was the right place.

590
00:40:38,103 --> 00:40:39,980
I was hoping you would...

591
00:40:40,063 --> 00:40:43,150
thank me or give me a reward.

592
00:40:43,233 --> 00:40:45,944
B-but why are you angry with me?

593
00:40:46,027 --> 00:40:48,989
Is it my fault
that someone informed them about it?

594
00:40:49,072 --> 00:40:50,282
How dare you!

595
00:40:50,365 --> 00:40:51,491
Divino!

596
00:40:51,575 --> 00:40:54,286
You must admit that she does have a point.

597
00:40:54,369 --> 00:40:55,579
Katarina.

598
00:40:57,038 --> 00:40:58,248
Think about it, Pa.

599
00:40:58,331 --> 00:40:59,749
Who knows about your plan?

600
00:40:59,833 --> 00:41:01,001
Oh, yeah!

601
00:41:01,084 --> 00:41:03,628
There's a traitor in this house.

602
00:41:03,712 --> 00:41:05,046
And that is for sure not me.

603
00:41:05,130 --> 00:41:06,381
I want them captured.

604
00:41:06,464 --> 00:41:09,301
And Gem is carrying my child, right?
I want them safe.

605
00:41:09,384 --> 00:41:11,845
Oh, well, it's definitely not me too.

606
00:41:11,928 --> 00:41:13,930
Neither would I.

607
00:41:14,014 --> 00:41:16,850
I want Ma'am Gem to be found

608
00:41:16,933 --> 00:41:18,768
so this can all end.

609
00:41:18,852 --> 00:41:24,441
Who else from your family
do you think would betray you?

610
00:41:36,328 --> 00:41:37,204
Hello.

611
00:41:37,287 --> 00:41:39,372
This is the Investigator
of the Homicide Division.

612
00:41:39,456 --> 00:41:40,916
<i>We have a murder case</i>

613
00:41:40,999 --> 00:41:43,126
<i>of a man who has not yet been identified.</i>

614
00:41:43,210 --> 00:41:45,045
Do you know this man?

615
00:41:46,296 --> 00:41:47,380
Who is he?

616
00:41:49,758 --> 00:41:52,677
I only know that his name is Leon.

617
00:41:52,761 --> 00:41:55,347
I don't know his last name.

618
00:41:55,931 --> 00:41:57,682
He's from Morocco.

619
00:41:57,766 --> 00:42:00,268
I used to work there,
but it was a long time ago.

620
00:42:01,269 --> 00:42:03,438
Well, we weren't close.

621
00:42:06,233 --> 00:42:09,653
Ms. Loyola, why did he have
a lot of messages sent to your number?

622
00:42:10,695 --> 00:42:13,448
Your active phone number
is saved on his phone.

623
00:42:13,531 --> 00:42:16,243
Others are out of service.

624
00:42:16,326 --> 00:42:18,578
He was trying to extort me.

625
00:42:19,621 --> 00:42:22,040
He was asking me to give him

626
00:42:22,123 --> 00:42:23,875
one million pesos.

627
00:42:24,292 --> 00:42:25,961
Why?

628
00:42:27,337 --> 00:42:28,505
I have...

629
00:42:29,130 --> 00:42:33,009
I have some pictures and...

630
00:42:33,635 --> 00:42:36,638
and a sex video in Morocco...

631
00:42:37,472 --> 00:42:41,434
that he said he would spread online
if I didn't give him the money.

632
00:42:41,518 --> 00:42:44,854
But I don't really have
any lewd pictures or videos.

633
00:42:44,938 --> 00:42:47,315
And I don't have that much money, sir.

634
00:42:47,399 --> 00:42:50,235
Why did he try to extort you?

635
00:42:51,820 --> 00:42:55,740
Because... he knew
that my employers are very wealthy.

636
00:42:55,824 --> 00:42:57,325
Sir, he even told me

637
00:42:57,409 --> 00:43:00,662
to steal from my employers
and give him the money.

638
00:43:01,288 --> 00:43:03,290
And that's why I was ignoring him.

639
00:43:04,124 --> 00:43:07,460
That explains
why he called my number a lot.

640
00:43:07,544 --> 00:43:09,963
There are so many evil people, sir.

641
00:43:10,046 --> 00:43:11,214
Maybe...

642
00:43:11,840 --> 00:43:13,091
or most likely...

643
00:43:13,717 --> 00:43:16,720
he has a lot of other enemies
and other victims.

644
00:43:16,803 --> 00:43:18,805
But I swear, sir, I have nothing to do

645
00:43:18,888 --> 00:43:21,516
with the death of that bastard.
Please believe me, sir.

646
00:43:21,599 --> 00:43:24,519
Where were you
around 12:30 a.m. last night?

647
00:43:24,602 --> 00:43:27,647
Can anyone attest to your alibi,
Ms. Loyola?

648
00:43:28,440 --> 00:43:31,109
I can. I'm Attorney Ace Verona.

649
00:43:31,192 --> 00:43:32,569
I'm representing Ms. Loyola.

650
00:43:34,029 --> 00:43:36,031
Larajean has been working
for my family's business

651
00:43:36,114 --> 00:43:37,198
for quite a while now.

652
00:43:37,782 --> 00:43:39,659
If you want an alibi,

653
00:43:39,743 --> 00:43:42,495
she was at the jewelry store last night
working overtime.

654
00:43:42,579 --> 00:43:44,748
We have CCTVs and logbooks to prove that.

655
00:43:44,831 --> 00:43:47,876
She has been one of our best
and most trusted employees.

656
00:43:47,959 --> 00:43:49,210
Now, officer,

657
00:43:49,294 --> 00:43:52,005
if you don't have
sufficient probable cause to detain her

658
00:43:52,088 --> 00:43:54,174
or if you don't intend
to file formal charges

659
00:43:54,257 --> 00:43:55,675
within the next hour,

660
00:43:55,759 --> 00:43:57,635
I suggest my client be released.

661
00:43:57,719 --> 00:43:59,804
- This is SOP--
- Then SOP is over.

662
00:43:59,888 --> 00:44:01,890
She has already provided her statement.

663
00:44:02,515 --> 00:44:04,768
Now, if any of you have
any further questions,

664
00:44:04,851 --> 00:44:06,895
or if you need her
for a subsequent deposition,

665
00:44:06,978 --> 00:44:08,021
request it through me.

666
00:44:08,104 --> 00:44:09,606
Don't call her directly.

667
00:44:11,858 --> 00:44:13,193
Let's go, Larajean.

668
00:44:17,655 --> 00:44:18,656
<i>The Immigration confirmed</i>

669
00:44:18,740 --> 00:44:20,992
that Leon just recently
entered the country.

670
00:44:21,076 --> 00:44:23,828
Your statement has a ring of truth.

671
00:44:23,912 --> 00:44:25,246
He was there for a long time.

672
00:44:25,789 --> 00:44:28,625
Good thing there were no saved messages
that can be used against you.

673
00:44:29,125 --> 00:44:29,959
It's clear.

674
00:44:30,043 --> 00:44:31,628
But expect a call from the investigator

675
00:44:31,711 --> 00:44:32,962
in case something comes up.

676
00:44:33,046 --> 00:44:36,549
But for now, I think
you're no longer considered a suspect.

677
00:44:37,550 --> 00:44:40,303
Thank you, sir. Thank you.

678
00:44:42,055 --> 00:44:43,640
Uh, you can have your day off.

679
00:44:43,723 --> 00:44:45,058
I will tell Mama.

680
00:44:45,809 --> 00:44:47,060
Thank you, sir.

681
00:44:48,186 --> 00:44:49,437
Let me drive you home.

682
00:44:51,356 --> 00:44:54,943
No. I don't want to bother you.
No need, uh...

683
00:44:55,026 --> 00:44:58,988
You've done more than enough to help me.

684
00:44:59,072 --> 00:45:02,075
Uh, Larajean,
don't try to be shy and cute.

685
00:45:02,158 --> 00:45:03,660
It doesn't suit you.

686
00:45:12,544 --> 00:45:13,545
Eric.

687
00:45:13,962 --> 00:45:14,879
<i> Sir.</i>

688
00:45:15,380 --> 00:45:17,048
<i>We have Jorge.</i>

689
00:45:17,674 --> 00:45:19,092
<i>Where should we take him?</i>

690
00:45:50,582 --> 00:45:51,666
Enough!

691
00:45:52,250 --> 00:45:53,418
Jorge.

692
00:45:54,127 --> 00:45:56,546
My dear father-in-law...

693
00:45:56,629 --> 00:45:58,423
Who are you and Gem working with?

694
00:46:02,343 --> 00:46:04,554
- Speak!
- I don't know her name!

695
00:46:04,637 --> 00:46:06,681
- We only call her "Boss."
- Boss?

696
00:46:06,764 --> 00:46:07,640
"Her."

697
00:46:09,225 --> 00:46:11,519
- A woman.
- Yes, a lady!

698
00:46:11,603 --> 00:46:13,563
- Call her.
- I don't know her number.

699
00:46:13,646 --> 00:46:15,690
I call someone first. Emergency!

700
00:46:15,773 --> 00:46:17,734
I don't care. Call her.

701
00:46:23,865 --> 00:46:26,409
- Jorge.
- <i>I need to talk to Boss.</i>

702
00:46:26,493 --> 00:46:27,577
It's about Gem.

703
00:46:27,660 --> 00:46:29,162
I will call you back.

704
00:46:36,920 --> 00:46:38,838
Yes? Hello? Jorge?

705
00:46:40,465 --> 00:46:42,383
<i>- Jorge!</i>

706
00:46:43,134 --> 00:46:44,260
I don't know.

707
00:46:46,304 --> 00:46:47,639
It's like...

708
00:46:48,431 --> 00:46:51,518
I can't place the voice and the number.

709
00:46:51,601 --> 00:46:52,936
It's a woman.

710
00:46:53,019 --> 00:46:55,104
- Then call her again.
- No.

711
00:46:55,855 --> 00:46:57,941
She'll know that we have Jorge.

712
00:46:59,442 --> 00:47:00,944
I have a plan.

713
00:47:03,404 --> 00:47:04,656
Untie him.

714
00:47:06,115 --> 00:47:07,200
Clean him up.

715
00:47:08,243 --> 00:47:09,494
And let him go.

716
00:47:09,994 --> 00:47:11,162
What?

717
00:47:11,579 --> 00:47:12,747
And follow him.

718
00:47:13,456 --> 00:47:16,376
He will be our key to finding Teo and Gem.

719
00:47:16,960 --> 00:47:18,545
And trace the number.

720
00:47:23,800 --> 00:47:25,301
That's what he said.

721
00:47:25,385 --> 00:47:27,178
Then he called again.

722
00:47:27,262 --> 00:47:30,390
When I spoke to him, no one answered.

723
00:47:30,473 --> 00:47:31,599
He was just listening.

724
00:47:31,683 --> 00:47:32,850
What about Divino?

725
00:47:32,934 --> 00:47:34,310
I don't know, ma'am.

726
00:47:34,394 --> 00:47:36,479
I've never talked to the judge

727
00:47:36,563 --> 00:47:39,524
for him to recognize my voice.

728
00:47:39,607 --> 00:47:40,525
What if...

729
00:47:40,608 --> 00:47:42,694
the judge already has Jorge?

730
00:47:42,777 --> 00:47:44,028
He's going to talk.

731
00:47:44,112 --> 00:47:45,154
I know.

732
00:47:45,238 --> 00:47:47,991
But what do they know about me?

733
00:47:48,074 --> 00:47:50,034
<i>He doesn't know me.</i>

734
00:47:50,118 --> 00:47:51,953
We've only talked on the phone.

735
00:47:52,036 --> 00:47:55,164
But he has seen and met you before.

736
00:47:55,248 --> 00:47:56,791
Take precautions.

737
00:47:56,874 --> 00:47:58,835
Get all the important files.

738
00:47:58,918 --> 00:48:00,253
Leave that place

739
00:48:00,336 --> 00:48:02,213
<i>and wait until I call you again.</i>

740
00:48:10,346 --> 00:48:12,265
It's good. It's cold.

741
00:48:13,850 --> 00:48:15,602
- It's a bit...
- A bit dry.

742
00:48:15,685 --> 00:48:17,145
- Sweet.
- Yeah.

743
00:48:17,228 --> 00:48:18,730
- Sweet.
- Mm.

744
00:48:18,813 --> 00:48:21,232
Oh, heavens gracious!

745
00:48:21,316 --> 00:48:22,900
- What?
- Nine o'clock!

746
00:48:24,736 --> 00:48:26,404
Does Katarina know?

747
00:48:26,487 --> 00:48:27,905
It could be about business.

748
00:48:27,989 --> 00:48:30,825
Business? Looking like that?

749
00:48:31,367 --> 00:48:34,579
I can smell a mistress a mile away.

750
00:48:34,662 --> 00:48:36,372
What are you doing?

751
00:48:43,796 --> 00:48:45,965
Somebody called me earlier.

752
00:48:48,426 --> 00:48:49,761
Unknown number.

753
00:48:50,887 --> 00:48:52,972
The call came from a foreign country.

754
00:48:53,556 --> 00:48:55,141
I'll have it traced.

755
00:48:55,224 --> 00:48:56,309
When?

756
00:48:57,185 --> 00:48:58,519
This is urgent.

757
00:48:59,228 --> 00:49:01,147
What if it's connected to Gem?

758
00:49:01,814 --> 00:49:02,899
Gem?

759
00:49:02,982 --> 00:49:05,735
You know what she did to my family.

760
00:49:05,818 --> 00:49:08,029
I have every reason to doubt

761
00:49:08,112 --> 00:49:11,115
that she ruined
the operations of the shipments.

762
00:49:11,199 --> 00:49:13,701
- I don't think--
- Come to think of it.

763
00:49:13,785 --> 00:49:16,287
With all your connections in Morocco,

764
00:49:16,371 --> 00:49:18,414
you didn't find anything about Yana.

765
00:49:19,832 --> 00:49:22,001
I asked you to look into it, right?

766
00:49:23,044 --> 00:49:27,131
Maybe... the enemy is really powerful.

767
00:49:27,965 --> 00:49:32,136
Or maybe
the enemy is just within my territory

768
00:49:32,220 --> 00:49:33,221
all along.

769
00:49:36,766 --> 00:49:38,685
If so, what would you do?

770
00:49:39,519 --> 00:49:41,437
That goes without saying.

771
00:49:43,731 --> 00:49:46,401
A punishment worse than death.

772
00:49:47,568 --> 00:49:50,071
Especially for those who will betray me.

773
00:49:52,865 --> 00:49:54,033
I have to go.

774
00:50:24,439 --> 00:50:25,606
This is a problem for us.

775
00:50:25,690 --> 00:50:27,608
They have Jorge.

776
00:50:27,692 --> 00:50:28,860
Did he snitch?

777
00:50:30,445 --> 00:50:31,738
<i>No.</i>

778
00:50:31,821 --> 00:50:35,158
<i>I don't know,</i>
<i>but I'm sure he said something.</i>

779
00:50:35,241 --> 00:50:37,160
I also have to leave immediately.

780
00:50:37,243 --> 00:50:39,579
Yana, let me know if you need my help.

781
00:50:39,662 --> 00:50:42,707
I'm fine. Do you need any help?

782
00:50:42,790 --> 00:50:44,208
I can handle this.

783
00:50:44,292 --> 00:50:46,294
<i>I'll contact you again.</i>

784
00:50:46,377 --> 00:50:47,962
But if I don't,

785
00:50:48,045 --> 00:50:49,964
don't worry about me.

786
00:50:50,047 --> 00:50:51,841
Proceed with your plan.

787
00:50:57,430 --> 00:51:00,183
It looks like Divino found out
the boss's real identity.

788
00:51:01,434 --> 00:51:05,605
What?
Has Rita been caught for her shenanigans?

789
00:51:05,688 --> 00:51:07,398
Then that's good.

790
00:51:07,482 --> 00:51:10,610
Let the Veronas catch her.

791
00:51:10,693 --> 00:51:11,694
Pa!

792
00:51:11,778 --> 00:51:13,237
She got herself in that mess!

793
00:51:13,321 --> 00:51:14,822
She should get herself out.

794
00:51:14,906 --> 00:51:16,616
She got us all involved in this.

795
00:51:16,699 --> 00:51:19,911
Listen. No one will help her, okay?

796
00:51:20,828 --> 00:51:22,038
Teo...

797
00:51:24,415 --> 00:51:26,083
Gem, I don't know her anymore.

798
00:51:28,044 --> 00:51:30,129
She didn't even try to get to know us.

799
00:51:31,088 --> 00:51:32,757
She's a totally different person now, Gem.

800
00:51:32,840 --> 00:51:34,217
I don't want to ruin our plan.

801
00:51:34,300 --> 00:51:36,385
We will continue with our plan.

802
00:51:36,469 --> 00:51:37,845
But let's save her.

803
00:51:37,929 --> 00:51:39,889
- We're running out of time--
- I know, Teo.

804
00:51:39,972 --> 00:51:42,391
But she did a lot for me
and my mom back then.

805
00:51:43,684 --> 00:51:46,187
If she won't come along,
then I won't come either.

806
00:52:16,843 --> 00:52:19,512
You really have no shame.

807
00:52:20,471 --> 00:52:22,557
I see you're no longer hiding.

808
00:52:22,640 --> 00:52:24,058
Divino has already left.

809
00:52:24,559 --> 00:52:27,478
- Talk to your husband.
- No, I'm talking to you.

810
00:52:29,230 --> 00:52:31,315
I already agreed to your setup,

811
00:52:31,399 --> 00:52:34,277
but I do not want you
displaying your disgusting affair

812
00:52:34,360 --> 00:52:35,653
here in the Philippines.

813
00:52:35,736 --> 00:52:37,238
Know your place.

814
00:52:38,489 --> 00:52:41,242
My place? You want me to know my place?

815
00:52:42,159 --> 00:52:43,828
It's in Divino's heart.

816
00:52:45,329 --> 00:52:47,373
Oh, come on, Pearl.

817
00:52:47,456 --> 00:52:50,543
He works with me
and goes on vacations with me.

818
00:52:50,626 --> 00:52:53,671
We eat and even shower together.

819
00:52:53,754 --> 00:52:56,132
And when night comes, we sleep together.

820
00:52:56,591 --> 00:52:58,759
Can you say you're doing all that too?

821
00:52:58,843 --> 00:52:59,927
No, right?

822
00:53:01,178 --> 00:53:03,264
Because Divino chose me.

823
00:53:04,265 --> 00:53:06,559
And even if you turn the world
upside down,

824
00:53:06,642 --> 00:53:09,270
Divino will still choose me.

825
00:53:12,273 --> 00:53:15,484
Yes,
he could have chosen you tonight.

826
00:53:15,568 --> 00:53:17,653
Or maybe he'll choose you again tomorrow.

827
00:53:17,737 --> 00:53:20,573
But he chose a life with me, Pearl.

828
00:53:20,656 --> 00:53:23,117
And you're just enjoying moments.

829
00:53:23,200 --> 00:53:25,995
Moments don't make a life, Pearl.

830
00:53:26,078 --> 00:53:28,831
It just adds to your delusions.

831
00:53:28,915 --> 00:53:31,083
I am the wife.

832
00:53:31,167 --> 00:53:34,587
And whatever delusion you feed yourself,

833
00:53:34,670 --> 00:53:38,215
in the end, the wife always wins.

834
00:53:38,299 --> 00:53:41,427
You're right. The wife always wins.

835
00:53:41,510 --> 00:53:44,138
But I might as well be his wife,

836
00:53:44,889 --> 00:53:50,019
because I am your husband's forever.

837
00:53:50,102 --> 00:53:52,605
What a lame clapback, Pearl.

838
00:53:52,688 --> 00:53:56,609
Just like your lame and pathetic life.

839
00:53:58,069 --> 00:53:58,945
Tch!

840
00:54:03,157 --> 00:54:06,369
This is my territory, Pearl!
My town!

841
00:54:06,452 --> 00:54:11,248
So I suggest that you leave this town
while you still have legs to do so.

842
00:54:11,332 --> 00:54:13,876
Because the next time I see you,

843
00:54:13,960 --> 00:54:15,544
I might just leave you crippled!

844
00:54:15,628 --> 00:54:19,131
And I'll make sure
that they drag you out of this town

845
00:54:19,215 --> 00:54:22,802
in a way that is far less than dignified!

846
00:54:28,349 --> 00:54:30,434
Damn you, Divino!

847
00:54:30,518 --> 00:54:33,729
Damn you! Rot in hell, Pearl!

848
00:54:36,732 --> 00:54:38,234
Freaking cheaters!

849
00:54:44,615 --> 00:54:45,950
U-uh... Madam?

850
00:54:47,368 --> 00:54:48,285
Madam?

851
00:54:51,622 --> 00:54:53,708
Do I look like I need company?

852
00:54:53,791 --> 00:54:54,875
Sorry, madam.

853
00:54:54,959 --> 00:54:57,378
I just saw this
among your stuff over there.

854
00:54:57,461 --> 00:54:58,713
I thought you might need it.

855
00:55:00,923 --> 00:55:03,676
Well, you're damn right.
I need that drink.

856
00:55:03,759 --> 00:55:05,636
And guns! And ammo!

857
00:55:06,220 --> 00:55:10,725
Unlimited ammo for people
who have no ounce of shame!

858
00:55:12,935 --> 00:55:16,272
I just had the most draining confrontation

859
00:55:16,355 --> 00:55:18,399
with that mistress of Divino.

860
00:55:19,025 --> 00:55:20,943
I came to confront them at a restaurant

861
00:55:21,027 --> 00:55:24,113
after a friend sent me
a picture of them having dinner.

862
00:55:24,196 --> 00:55:25,573
And guess what?

863
00:55:25,656 --> 00:55:28,617
They were having dinner
in our favorite restaurant!

864
00:55:29,702 --> 00:55:31,871
She even had the audacity to tell me

865
00:55:31,954 --> 00:55:34,415
Divino loves her more,

866
00:55:34,498 --> 00:55:37,084
which is okay! Acceptable!

867
00:55:37,168 --> 00:55:42,006
But to tell me that she deserves
my place in Divino's life

868
00:55:42,089 --> 00:55:44,550
is totally unforgivable!

869
00:55:46,135 --> 00:55:48,679
Uh... madam, is that her?

870
00:55:48,763 --> 00:55:50,431
The one in the photo?

871
00:55:52,099 --> 00:55:53,017
Well, yeah.

872
00:55:56,270 --> 00:55:57,104
What?

873
00:56:05,362 --> 00:56:06,864
- Oh, my!
- What?

874
00:56:08,282 --> 00:56:12,286
Ma'am... are you sure
that's the judge's mistress?

875
00:56:12,369 --> 00:56:13,454
Of course!

876
00:56:13,537 --> 00:56:17,041
What, you think
I'd crash out without making sure?

877
00:56:17,124 --> 00:56:20,336
- You idiot.
- But ma'am, I know her.

878
00:56:20,419 --> 00:56:21,837
Th-that's Miss Rita!

879
00:56:21,921 --> 00:56:24,173
Who the hell is Rita?

880
00:56:27,510 --> 00:56:28,677
Jorge.

881
00:56:29,887 --> 00:56:32,473
Help me! Divino kidnapped me.

882
00:56:32,556 --> 00:56:33,891
And I got away!

883
00:56:38,729 --> 00:56:39,563
Ace.

884
00:56:40,731 --> 00:56:43,150
Wait, Pa. Listen.

885
00:56:43,234 --> 00:56:45,319
<i>That Pearl is here.</i>

886
00:56:46,821 --> 00:56:49,573
Jorge and your mistress know each other?

887
00:56:51,033 --> 00:56:52,701
Stay put, Ace.

888
00:56:53,285 --> 00:56:56,455
Wait for me. I'll deal with it.

889
00:57:02,211 --> 00:57:03,629
What does he know?

890
00:57:03,712 --> 00:57:06,590
They asked me about your name.

891
00:57:06,674 --> 00:57:08,509
I told them I don't know.

892
00:57:09,426 --> 00:57:11,178
They asked me who you were.

893
00:57:11,762 --> 00:57:14,765
I told them I only know you as "Boss."

894
00:57:15,516 --> 00:57:18,853
So, it's like...
they didn't get anything from me.

895
00:57:19,478 --> 00:57:20,646
And you escaped?

896
00:57:20,729 --> 00:57:23,065
Actually, they let me go.

897
00:57:23,149 --> 00:57:24,400
Shit, Jorge!

898
00:59:22,726 --> 00:59:23,560
It's over.

899
00:59:23,644 --> 00:59:24,645
<i>She's gone.</i>

900
00:59:24,728 --> 00:59:26,730
- Ma.
- We've gotten rid of the pest.

901
00:59:26,814 --> 00:59:30,317
<i>Wherever you go,</i>
<i>death follows you.</i>

902
00:59:30,401 --> 00:59:32,611
- So, what's your decision?
- We're all leaving.

903
00:59:32,695 --> 00:59:35,656
- We're going to Vietnam.
- Hello, Larajean?

904
00:59:35,739 --> 00:59:37,908
<i>We're leaving today.</i>

905
00:59:37,992 --> 00:59:39,660
Wh-where are you going?

906
00:59:39,743 --> 00:59:41,495
<i>Ronnie, Raya isn't part of our plan!</i>

907
00:59:41,578 --> 00:59:43,163
<i>She might've been sent by the Veronas.</i>

908
00:59:43,247 --> 00:59:45,749
Raya isn't like that.
Let's take her with us.

909
00:59:45,833 --> 00:59:47,793
Someone's coming!
Get in the car! Let's go!

910
00:59:47,876 --> 00:59:48,877
Hurry! Be careful!

911
00:59:48,961 --> 00:59:50,921
Teo, come out! There's nowhere to escape!
